steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Thinly slice the shallots
- Coarsely chop the  garlic 
- Coarsely chop the parsley

### Steps
1. Bring water to boil in large stockpot for noodles
2. Slice shallots; chop garlic and parsley (about 1 cup)
3. Season chicken with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
4. Preheat large sauté pan on medium-high 2–3 minutes
5. Pour oil in pan, then add chicken; cook 3–4 minutes on each side or until browned
6. Add shallots, garlic, and paprika; cook 2–3 minutes or until fragrant
7. Add pasta sauce and vinegar, then cover and reduce heat to low; simmer 15–18 minutes and until chicken is 185°F (for shreddable)
8. Meanwhile, cook noodles following package instructions
9. Drain well, then return noodles to pot
10. Add butter, 3/4 cup parsley, and remaining 1/2 teaspoon each salt and pepper; stir until butter is melted
11. Remove pan from heat and lightly shred chicken; stir in 1/2 cup yogurt
12. Divide noodles evenly among serving plates; top with even amounts chicken mixture and remaining yogurt
13. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup parsley; serve
